A pull request, or PR, is when you ask to add your branch changes into the main project.


Why developers use pull requests:

  To check code before adding it

  To catch mistakes
  
  To let teammates leave comments
  
  To keep main safe

  To show what changed


How to pull Request:

  Go here:
      
    At the top of your repository, you should see tabs like:
    
      Code | Issues | Pull requests | Actions | Projects | Wiki | Security | Insights
    
    Click:
    
      Pull requests

